# eslint.config.mjs patch — register jsx-a11y

Add the following to `eslint.config.mjs`. Order: after `eslint-plugin-react-hooks`, before any Next.js config.

```js
import jsxA11y from 'eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y';

export default [
  // ... existing config blocks ...

  // Accessibility — non-negotiable. Strict ruleset.
  {
    files: ['**/*.{tsx,jsx}'],
    plugins: { 'jsx-a11y': jsxA11y },
    rules: {
      ...jsxA11y.configs.strict.rules,

      // Project-specific overrides — keep this list short and justified.
      // Each line below is a deliberate exception; add reasoning as a comment.

      // shadcn's <Slot> pattern: child element provides the actual interactive role.
      // This rule fires false positives. The Radix primitives handle a11y correctly.
      'jsx-a11y/no-noninteractive-element-interactions': ['error', {
        handlers: ['onClick', 'onMouseDown', 'onMouseUp', 'onKeyPress', 'onKeyDown', 'onKeyUp'],
        body: [],
      }],

      // Anchors are routinely rendered with onClick + href for client routing.
      // The Next.js <Link> handles this correctly — accept it.
      'jsx-a11y/anchor-is-valid': ['error', {
        components: ['Link'],
        specialLink: ['hrefLeft', 'hrefRight'],
        aspects: ['invalidHref', 'preferButton'],
      }],
    },
  },
];
```

That's it. Save, restart your editor's ESLint server, errors appear in `LoginForm.tsx` lines that need attention.

If a rule is firing on a pattern that's genuinely correct, document the exception:

```tsx
{/* eslint-disable-next-line jsx-a11y/no-static-element-interactions -- Pure presentational click target; aria-hidden surrounding */}
<div onClick={...} />
```

Per-line disables require a reason after the `--`. CI rejects bare disables. (Configure via `eslint-comments` if not already on.)
